.TH "kbuffer_translate_data" 9 "kbuffer_translate_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kbuffer_translate_data \- read raw data to get a record
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" kbuffer_translate_data
.BI "(int swap "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "swap" 12
Set to 1 if bytes in words need to be swapped when read
.IP "data" 12
The raw data to read
.IP "size" 12
Address to store the size of the event data.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a pointer to the event data. To determine the entire
record size (record metadata + data) just add the difference between
\fIdata\fP and the returned value to \fIsize\fP.
